Name: flattened rice / pohe
description: ible,dehusked rice which is flattened into flat light dry flakes,these flakes of rice swell when added to liquid,whether hot or cold,as they absorb water,milk,or any other liquids. the thicknesses of these flakes vary between almost translucently thin (the more expensive varieties) to nearly four times thicker than a normal rice grain.
